						<h3>The Yin &amp; Yang of Advisory</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>YIN:</strong> <em>Techie:</em> Advisory is driven by advanced technology and we do more than a little development of our own. A high level of tech fluency is mandatory.<br /><br />

							<strong>YANG:</strong> <em>Human:</em> Advisors work under pressure. You need to have empathy for the situation and build confidence in those around you, while remaining objective and clear.
						  </li>
							<li><strong>YIN:</strong> <em>Sudden:</em> Advisory offers engagements that are highly complex, time sensitive and reactive, such as finding fraud or identifying cyber leaks. <br /><br />

							<strong>YANG:</strong> <em>Consistent:</em> Advisory also offers long-term engagements that leverage risk in other ways, such as transforming processes and speeding time to market.
						  </li>
							<li><strong>YIN:</strong> <em> Travel:</em> Private sector advisors work off-site alongside their clients and team members, often in distant cities and sometimes other countries. <br /><br />

							<strong>YANG:</strong> <em>Home base:</em> Federal practice advisors work in and around the D.C. area, only occasionally traveling for work.<br />
						  </li>
					</ul>
